h3. Problem Definition

The customer would like to be able to hide the "Customer Channel" session from the sidebar, so that his agents shouldn't see the links to his portal. Screen below

!screenshot-1.png|thumbnail!
h3. Suggested Solution

Have an option to remove it from the UI
h3. Workaround

(i) Notice, the suggested customisation below is unsupported and is provided as a best effort only. Please test thoroughly on a test and staging instance before applying in production as undesired consequences can occur.

In general, it should be possible to hide certain elements on [any web page|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirakb/how-to-hide-elements-in-jira-using-css-or-javascript-958774526.html]

The following announcement banner code is known to work on Jira Service Desk 4.9 (might need to be adjusted for previous or later versions of Jira)
{code:java}
<Style type="text/css">
a.aui-nav-item.js-customer-channels.js-no-select {
    display: none !important; 
    }
</style>
{code}

If the banner doesn't work, please follow the [linked article|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirakb/how-to-hide-elements-in-jira-using-css-or-javascript-958774526.html] on the detailed explanation on how the css code is formed.
Feel free to add your comment here or post a question the [Atlassian Community|https://community.atlassian.com/] forum if it doesn't work out of the box and need adustments

