h3. Summary

If an approval step is added to a workflow where the name contains a slash (e.g. "Workflow for Project1/Project2"), the configuration popup will not open, making it so that the user is not able to set up the approval properly.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a new workflow, with its name having a slash on it;
# Associate this workflow with a JIRA Service Desk project;
# Add a approval step to any status on the workflow;

h3. Expected Results

The *Add approval* configuration window will pop up.

h3. Actual Results
The *Add approval* configuration window will not show up, and bad requests (400) are shown on the HAR file.

